== Exercises

. Create an array with strings in the format `BOOKNAME` -` BOOKGENDER` - `AUTHOR'S NAME`
* Tip: Use a function `map`

. Build an array of objects from an array of books. Each object must contain an author property, with the name of the person who authored the book, and a property acts at the age of that person when the book was released. The array should be ordered by age, that is, from the youngest person to the oldest person considering their age when the book was released.
* Tip: use the `map`, `sort` functions

. Create an array of all objects that belong to the scientific or fantasy category.
* Tip: use as a function filter;

. Create an array sorted by books with more than 60 years of publication and sort by the oldest book.
* Tip: use the filter and `sort` functions

. Create an array in alphabetical order with just the names of all the people who wrote science fiction or fantasy.

. Create an array with the name of all books with more than 60 years of publication.

. Find the name of the book written by the person whose registered name starts with three initials. Tip: each initial ends with a period.